OL,3,CGuernsey law updated to include new,
OL,4,Cspecific offence for domestic abuse
OL,6,FChanges include:
OL,8,FTraining will now be put in place
OL,9,Fahead of the legislation "going live"
OL,10,F- which will happen upon being given
OL,11,FRoyal Assent in the coming months.
OL,13,FDeputy Sue Aldwell, who lead on
OL,14,Fdomestic abuse and sexual assault for
OL,15,Fthe committee, added she was pleased
OL,16,Fto "move the Bailiwick past the days
OL,17,Fwhere certain types of offenders fall
OL,18,Fthrough gaps in our then-outdated
OL,19,Flegislation".
